==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: -footer
<hw>-foot"er</hw> <pos>suff.</pos> <def>a suffix designating
<sig>something with a length of (so many) feet</sig>; -- used only in
combinations with a numerical prefix; <as>as, he is a
six-<ex>footer</ex>; the golfer sank a <ex>40-footer</ex>; his yacht is
a <ex>60-footer</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

